  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The post-electoral crisis in Cote d&#x2019;Ivoire resulted in a large influx of refugees into Liberia. It was reported by the Liberian government that an estimated 25,000 Ivorian refugees crossed over to Liberia at the time applications were received by JOAC, with more expected in the coming days and weeks, particularly given the recent spike in violent unrest and the discovery of a third mass grave in Cote d&#x2019;Ivoire. JOAC awarded Action Aid &#xA3;30,000 for food and non-food items, such as farming inputs, hygiene kits and kitchen kits, Tearfund &#xA3;30,000 for the provision of water and sanitation; and British Red Cross &#xA3;30,000 for household kits and shelter materials.</narrative>
  </description>
